Questions arising after the accident: Are stewards on the bus illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long-distance bus is forbidden
In the context of the tragic accident of the Student Agency bus near Padua, Italy, the question arises whether stewards and passengers can move around inside the bus during the journey.
"If the law is to be strictly and formally enforced, the work of a steward is contrary to the traffic law", says Transport Ministry spokesman Karel Hanzelka.
The accident in question, in which a 22-year-old hostess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck who crossed the bus path.
Unfortunately, the girl was sitting next to the driver in the most dangerous seat of the vehicle at the time, although she had two more seats available.
The bus may crash or even brake suddenly, even while the steward serves coffee or distributes newspapers.
What matters is whether the bus is in accordance with its technical file and has standing seats or not.
If this standing-seat equipment is not approved, passengers must remain seated.
Student Agency long-distance buses do not have standing seats, as the company's director Radim Jančura confirmed to Aktuálně.cz.
"This is a matter we have discussed with the ministry and at first it forbids any movement of passengers.
Then they cancelled it and we got that passengers can go to the toilet during the journey provided they have their own seat", he revealed his position.
The Steward Is Ignored by the Law
"There is no single legal interpretation of the steward role - no legal requirement deals with this role.
On the other hand, no legal requirement prevents the carrier from offering services.
The road transport law only knows the term 'vehicle receiver' and does not define its rights and duties,' adds Hanzelka.
On the contrary, Josef Pokorný, the Director of the Department of Road Traffic, believes that the law deals sufficiently with the problem.
"It all depends on whether the bus has permission to offer standing seats in its approval.
It's all in there", he said.
Buses are divided into urban areas, where there are standing seats and a maximum speed limit, interurban areas with standing seats and a higher permitted speed and long distance buses without standing seats with the highest permitted maximum speed and seats with seat belts.
Like on a plane, says an expert
Jaroslav Hořín, an expert at BESIP (road traffic safety) on safety in transport, does not see the movement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"There is no danger in regular traffic, and the situation can be compared to that of the airline.
Here too, it is not certain when a turbulence will occur and the air host may hit her head".
"But if the bus had stopped suddenly, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
Just like a city bus or a tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of stewards through internal prescriptions,' he said, adding that the issue was not settled from a legal point of view.
Jančura is ready to abolish these services
Student Agency is the only bus operator to offer steward services.
He hires two hundred.
Even after the accident, the manager doesn't consider their job a risky one.
"However, as soon as I feel that this is a risky profession, I will remove it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and diary on board.
It would also reduce costs", he said.
The reason for the absence of stewards in its vehicles is a safety concern, as stated by Alexei Litvine, the director of Asiana, which has a very small number of lines compared to SA.
"We don't have any hostesses. We've been fighting them since the beginning.
Sooner or later it will end up in a fatal accident", he told Týden.cz a year ago.
A great tragedy has happened
A young hostess from the Plzeň area, who had been working for the company for two years, died in the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably left the emergency stop lane without using a flashlight and blocked the bus's path.
The driver of the latter tried to avoid him by means of a sudden maneuver, but he rubbed him on his right side.
Jančura denies that the two seats reserved for the stewards' rest have been sold.
"In the case of long-distance lines, it is not possible to reserve these seats, they are blocked".
The company plans to file a complaint against the truck driver.
The agency will not wait for the court's decision to compensate the girl's family, but it will also count on the perpetrator for financial compensation.
A change in the law?
Not in sight
An amendment to the law, which has been being worked out for more than a year by a group of 30 experts from the Ministry of Transport, could provide details on the travel of stewards on the bus.
"But it has not reached any conclusion on this point.
In fact, it is not too interested in buses, but rather in the point system, the maximum speed on the motorway and the use of the mobile phone while driving", says Hořín.
"The Ministry of Transport does not consider stewards' activities as something that would fundamentally jeopardize passenger safety", concluded Hanzelka, adding that the safety control of buses is under the control of the police and the Office for Occupational Safety.
