Under the law, the Treasury Secretariat can implement a combined strategy: it can simultaneously purchase doubtful claims, mortgage and doubtful mortgage securities, and other types of 'toxic' claims.
The relevant authorities of the Ministry said that the purchases could be made through an auction, but also directly.
The rule gives the companies concerned the opportunity to participate in an insurance scheme, where the Treasury Secretariat guarantees the tools at the root of the concerns, for which the companies will have paid a premium equivalent to the foreseeable damage.
Henry Paulson said the law provides the necessary tools to spend $700 billion on the urgent needs of the financial system, whether it's the massive repurchase of doubtful debts, their insurance, or avoiding the risk of the system causing the collapse of one or another major financial institution.
"We will take the necessary measures to be ready for the implementation of the law as soon as it is signed", he added.
On the other hand, bank executives who are in bad shape and waiting for state help can expect their departure allowances, simply called the transatlantic gold parachute, to be capped by the government.
The salary cap is mentioned only in very specific cases and the limitations depend on how the Treasury Department provides assistance to the business.
The cap principle means that if the Treasury Department buys in an auction, they will levy a surplus tax on the gold parachute unless the discredited bank president retires.
Immediately after the doubtful debts are redeemed, the government will take aggressive action to ensure that the amount paid to the executives is not exaggerated.
The Commission has also proposed that the Commission should be able to take a decision on the implementation of the new rules on the protection of the environment and the environment.
This is the first time in the history of the United States that legal limits will be in place on the appointment of CEOs", said House Financial Services Committee Chairman Barney Frank, a Democrat.
In addition, the State acquires a right to acquire shares in the banks participating in the scheme, thus reducing the risk to taxpayers, as they may even be winning the deal once the economy and with it the saved banks are back on their feet.
The bill states that within the next five years, the President must submit to Congress a proposal that will determine how the losses will be repaid to taxpayers, from the financial sector.
