According to the opposition candidate in the 2006 presidential election, it is desirable that this remains the case, despite the fact that "the government has been afraid in this weightless parliament of bringing in even one opponent".
The opposition does not plan to protest the results, but rather tries to convey its message to the voters about the need for economic reforms.
