"Because of the country's debt and the rising trade deficit, the collapse of social security, 'called the silence of a cemetery,' is now only a matter of time", says Milinkevitch.
Unlike the opposition politician, Russian observers have called the elections democratic.
Sergey Lebedev, head of the mission of the Commonwealth of Independent States, told the Russian news agency Ria Novosti: "People do not believe in words but in deeds". Thus, the absence of opposition is only proof of the maturity of Belarusian voters.
